node.text:
Meet the kung fu master 👀

Mantids are born with excellent eyesight. However, their keen eyes are no equal match for that of a hungry jumping spider. But they do have one trick up their sleeve when it comes to self-defence: partaking in a bit of kung-fu. This self-defence mechanism serves to confuse its predator, making the insect appear bigger than it actually is. But, the fight to stay alive doesn’t end there…

node.text:
Jeremy thought it might be time to buy some tweezers... 🐦⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Black-throated parrotbill⁣s (Suthora nipalensis) are found in the Himalayas and in various locations in south-east Asia. They travel in fast-moving flocks and feed on insects, bits of bamboo and bamboo buds.⁣⁣
⁣⁣
#EarthCapture by @bimalbhaskar_wildlife⁣⁣

Put on your dancing shoes 💃

The male bowerbird (Sericulus ardens) builds and decorates his bower to attract the attention of females. Once a female pays his bower a visit, he will sing loudly and put on a spectacular performance to seal the deal. And this dance is really quite something...
